{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-js","path":"/repair-joycon","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<h1 id=\"context\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#context\" aria-label=\"context permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Context</h1>\n<p>Done! I finally got the infamous joycon drift on both joycons of my switch. As a reminder, for what joycon drift is, see <a href=\"https://www.nintendo.com/en-gb/Support/Repair/Joy-Con-Control-Sticks-Are-Not-Responding-or-Respond-Incorrectly-responsiveness-syndrome-or-so-called-drifting--1867803.html\">here</a>.<br>\nIt doesn't really prevent me from playing but it remains very annoying and sometimes even handicapping in certain games, so I started thinking about replacing or repairing my joycons.</p>\n<h1 id=\"tools\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#tools\" aria-label=\"tools permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Tools</h1>\n<p>Of course this is a problem encountered by all switch users at some point, so there are plenty of tutorials/videos on the internet.<br>\nWhat came out of the resources I consulted is that I needed two specific screwdrivers:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Y00 Triwing Screwdriver</li>\n<li>PH000 Phillips Screwdriver</li>\n</ul>\n<p>At first I wanted to only get these two screwdrivers and use a piece of cardboard paper (like a business card) that is supposed to be placed just under the joycon. But I had trouble finding these two screwdrivers on their own (aside from Chinese sites like Aliexpress which I don't want to use...)<br>\nSo I went with this <a href=\"https://www.amazon.ca/gp/product/B08CS7DS5V/ref=ppx_yo_dt_b_asin_title_o00_s00?ie=UTF8&#x26;psc=1\">pack</a> for 20 CAD ! Maybe a little expensive but it has everything inside:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Y00 Triwing Screwdriver</li>\n<li>PH000 Phillips Screwdriver</li>\n<li>4 new joysticks</li>\n<li>A tweezer</li>\n<li>A \"Plastic crowbar\"</li>\n<li>Various hardware (L/R button springs, Slider Lock, screws, etc.)</li>\n<li>Cosmetics for the joycons</li>\n</ul>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 850px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/62c092bef9391375c7240439abee45ec/62aaf/full_box.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 75.11737089201877%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"full box\"\n        title=\"full box\"\n        src=\"/static/62c092bef9391375c7240439abee45ec/8a34a/full_box.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/62c092bef9391375c7240439abee45ec/08b27/full_box.jpg 213w,\n/static/62c092bef9391375c7240439abee45ec/6f6b2/full_box.jpg 425w,\n/static/62c092bef9391375c7240439abee45ec/8a34a/full_box.jpg 850w,\n/static/62c092bef9391375c7240439abee45ec/63107/full_box.jpg 1275w,\n/static/62c092bef9391375c7240439abee45ec/62aaf/full_box.jpg 1280w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 850px) 100vw, 850px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<h1 id=\"repair\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#repair\" aria-label=\"repair permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Repair</h1>\n<p>Ok now that we're equipped, it's time to get to work! To do this, you need to clearly distinguish the right joycon from the left one as they are assembled differently.<br>\nI think you should count about 30 minutes for both joycons to be safe.</p>\n<h2 id=\"right-joycon\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#right-joycon\" aria-label=\"right joycon permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Right Joycon</h2>\n<p>We will first remove the 4 screws circled in the photo below:</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 850px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/953c0462e2beeeb94da5f70c7b0ddd80/fb816/first_screw.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 133.33333333333331%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"first screw\"\n        title=\"first screw\"\n        src=\"/static/953c0462e2beeeb94da5f70c7b0ddd80/8a34a/first_screw.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/953c0462e2beeeb94da5f70c7b0ddd80/08b27/first_screw.jpg 213w,\n/static/953c0462e2beeeb94da5f70c7b0ddd80/6f6b2/first_screw.jpg 425w,\n/static/953c0462e2beeeb94da5f70c7b0ddd80/8a34a/first_screw.jpg 850w,\n/static/953c0462e2beeeb94da5f70c7b0ddd80/fb816/first_screw.jpg 960w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 850px) 100vw, 850px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>Once the 4 screws are removed, slide the \"plastic crowbar\" into the gap that has appeared after removing the screws:</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 850px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/16f890d9d78e6e6e459b399ad64ebd78/67200/unplug.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 133.33333333333331%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"unplug\"\n        title=\"unplug\"\n        src=\"/static/16f890d9d78e6e6e459b399ad64ebd78/8a34a/unplug.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/16f890d9d78e6e6e459b399ad64ebd78/08b27/unplug.jpg 213w,\n/static/16f890d9d78e6e6e459b399ad64ebd78/6f6b2/unplug.jpg 425w,\n/static/16f890d9d78e6e6e459b399ad64ebd78/8a34a/unplug.jpg 850w,\n/static/16f890d9d78e6e6e459b399ad64ebd78/67200/unplug.jpg 961w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 850px) 100vw, 850px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>Then simply <strong>carefully</strong> open the joycon and here is its content:</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 646px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/6af3f7a3644c190f86fcd354a3de9200/82797/fisrt_open.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 88.26291079812205%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"fisrt open\"\n        title=\"fisrt open\"\n        src=\"/static/6af3f7a3644c190f86fcd354a3de9200/82797/fisrt_open.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/6af3f7a3644c190f86fcd354a3de9200/08b27/fisrt_open.jpg 213w,\n/static/6af3f7a3644c190f86fcd354a3de9200/6f6b2/fisrt_open.jpg 425w,\n/static/6af3f7a3644c190f86fcd354a3de9200/82797/fisrt_open.jpg 646w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 646px) 100vw, 646px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>You can notice that the two parts are connected with flat flexible cables. Now you need to remove the battery, gently push at the area circled in red.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 850px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/6125f2f94a74156411c3b00f682c1121/fb816/remove_battery.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 133.33333333333331%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"remove battery\"\n        title=\"remove battery\"\n        src=\"/static/6125f2f94a74156411c3b00f682c1121/8a34a/remove_battery.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/6125f2f94a74156411c3b00f682c1121/08b27/remove_battery.jpg 213w,\n/static/6125f2f94a74156411c3b00f682c1121/6f6b2/remove_battery.jpg 425w,\n/static/6125f2f94a74156411c3b00f682c1121/8a34a/remove_battery.jpg 850w,\n/static/6125f2f94a74156411c3b00f682c1121/fb816/remove_battery.jpg 960w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 850px) 100vw, 850px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>To get this:</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 850px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/81b59f57a7d669648d2d6b3ebaada005/fb816/without_battery.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 133.33333333333331%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"without battery\"\n        title=\"without battery\"\n        src=\"/static/81b59f57a7d669648d2d6b3ebaada005/8a34a/without_battery.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/81b59f57a7d669648d2d6b3ebaada005/08b27/without_battery.jpg 213w,\n/static/81b59f57a7d669648d2d6b3ebaada005/6f6b2/without_battery.jpg 425w,\n/static/81b59f57a7d669648d2d6b3ebaada005/8a34a/without_battery.jpg 850w,\n/static/81b59f57a7d669648d2d6b3ebaada005/fb816/without_battery.jpg 960w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 850px) 100vw, 850px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>From this point you will need to remove the 5 circled screws to be able to remove the battery cover:</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 850px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/4de449b7a3732bb96afe06fa07a3cbfa/fb816/without_battery_cache.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 133.33333333333331%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"without battery cache\"\n        title=\"without battery cache\"\n        src=\"/static/4de449b7a3732bb96afe06fa07a3cbfa/8a34a/without_battery_cache.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/4de449b7a3732bb96afe06fa07a3cbfa/08b27/without_battery_cache.jpg 213w,\n/static/4de449b7a3732bb96afe06fa07a3cbfa/6f6b2/without_battery_cache.jpg 425w,\n/static/4de449b7a3732bb96afe06fa07a3cbfa/8a34a/without_battery_cache.jpg 850w,\n/static/4de449b7a3732bb96afe06fa07a3cbfa/fb816/without_battery_cache.jpg 960w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 850px) 100vw, 850px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>This is where the most technical part will take place. First you will need to remove the 3 flat cables circled with a red square. To do this you need to perform the following two tasks:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Lift the small black tab (or grey for square #1)</li>\n<li>With your fingers or the tweezer, carefully remove the cable</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Then remove the two circled screws which will free the joystick and you can put one of the new joysticks in its place.</p>\n<p>And that's it! You just need to do all the previous operations in reverse and reassemble the joycon. Note that when inserting the flat cable I strongly recommend using the tweezer to be more precise:</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 850px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/4d6ca88fdb52bec098de4e68d856d000/62aaf/tweezer_ex.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 75.11737089201877%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"tweezer ex\"\n        title=\"tweezer ex\"\n        src=\"/static/4d6ca88fdb52bec098de4e68d856d000/8a34a/tweezer_ex.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/4d6ca88fdb52bec098de4e68d856d000/08b27/tweezer_ex.jpg 213w,\n/static/4d6ca88fdb52bec098de4e68d856d000/6f6b2/tweezer_ex.jpg 425w,\n/static/4d6ca88fdb52bec098de4e68d856d000/8a34a/tweezer_ex.jpg 850w,\n/static/4d6ca88fdb52bec098de4e68d856d000/63107/tweezer_ex.jpg 1275w,\n/static/4d6ca88fdb52bec098de4e68d856d000/62aaf/tweezer_ex.jpg 1280w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 850px) 100vw, 850px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>No need to push all the way in, once re-inserted you need to lower the plastic tab that was previously raised.</p>\n<p>NB: It's possible that the L/R button may escape (on the right in the photo above), you need to re-clip it before reassembling the shell that was removed in the first step.</p>\n<h2 id=\"left-joycon\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#left-joycon\" aria-label=\"left joycon permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Left Joycon</h2>\n<p>The left joycon is slightly different from the right one. Here are the differences:</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 850px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/fd7820e65fab12e583161e8e17e7bd3f/fb816/left_joycon.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 133.33333333333331%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"left joycon\"\n        title=\"left joycon\"\n        src=\"/static/fd7820e65fab12e583161e8e17e7bd3f/8a34a/left_joycon.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/fd7820e65fab12e583161e8e17e7bd3f/08b27/left_joycon.jpg 213w,\n/static/fd7820e65fab12e583161e8e17e7bd3f/6f6b2/left_joycon.jpg 425w,\n/static/fd7820e65fab12e583161e8e17e7bd3f/8a34a/left_joycon.jpg 850w,\n/static/fd7820e65fab12e583161e8e17e7bd3f/fb816/left_joycon.jpg 960w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 850px) 100vw, 850px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>Remove the 3 screws circled above. Once the battery cover is removed, here is what it looks like:</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 850px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/3c4cf11844cee112c46e909f91e7024a/62aaf/left_joycon_explode.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 75.11737089201877%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"left joycon explode\"\n        title=\"left joycon explode\"\n        src=\"/static/3c4cf11844cee112c46e909f91e7024a/8a34a/left_joycon_explode.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/3c4cf11844cee112c46e909f91e7024a/08b27/left_joycon_explode.jpg 213w,\n/static/3c4cf11844cee112c46e909f91e7024a/6f6b2/left_joycon_explode.jpg 425w,\n/static/3c4cf11844cee112c46e909f91e7024a/8a34a/left_joycon_explode.jpg 850w,\n/static/3c4cf11844cee112c46e909f91e7024a/63107/left_joycon_explode.jpg 1275w,\n/static/3c4cf11844cee112c46e909f91e7024a/62aaf/left_joycon_explode.jpg 1280w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 850px) 100vw, 850px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>Remove the two flat cables circled above then the two circled screws. And that's it!</p>\n<h1 id=\"conclusion\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#conclusion\" aria-label=\"conclusion permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Conclusion</h1>\n<p>Nothing too complicated in this joystick replacement on the joycons, you just need to be meticulous and well-equipped!</p>","timeToRead":4,"excerpt":"Context Done! I finally got the infamous joycon drift on both joycons of my switch. As a reminder, for what joycon drift is, see here. It…","fileAbsolutePath":"/home/runner/work/blog-beerus/blog-beerus/master/posts/2022/2022-09-08-repair-joycon/index.md","frontmatter":{"title":"Fix the \"joycon drift\" on my switch","categories":["Gaming"],"tags":["switch","DIY"],"thumbnail":{"childImageSharp":null,"extension":"svg","publicURL":"/static/e99c25331526c0cf669514698ece557c/thumbnail.svg"}}}},"pageContext":{"filter":"/^.*\\/\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2}-repair-joycon\\/.*$/"}},"staticQueryHashes":[]}